OL,6,F"To lose a person that you love so
OL,7,Funexpectedly and in such a horrific
OL,8,Fway has left an indescribable pain and
OL,9,Fa darkness in my life.
OL,11,F"Will was petrified of dying and to
OL,12,Fknow he was alone and died from such
OL,13,Fhorrendous injuries leaves me with
OL,14,Fsuch pain."
OL,16,FSentencing, Mrs Justice Steyn paid
OL,17,Ftribute to the bravery of William
OL,18,FBush's family, describing the victim
OL,19,Fas a "compassionate, loving, witty and
OL,20,Fvibrant young man" who was
OL,21,F"senselessly murdered."
